subject: Re: KGTMS Receipt numbers now broken
preview: Hi Joel,  Thank you for the confirmation.  Cheers,  Tanja

full_threads.body:
Hi Joel,

Thank you for the confirmation.

Cheers,

Tanja

Hi Tanja,

Hope all is well.
Confirming we have resent the new receipts.

Hi Joel,

Ok no problem, please go ahead with the send.

Cheers,

Tanja

Hi Tanja,

Due to the way the data is stored and the limitations of HTML in email browsers, we can't unfortunately remove the space between the dollar sign and the number. 

I hope that make sense and let us know if you want us to proceed with reissue of the receipt.

Hi Heath,

Please disregard my previous email - I only just saw the below now. 😊

The sample email looks good, is there any chance you can remove the space between the $ sign and the number?

Thank you,

Tanja

Hi Tanja,

We have sent to you the sample email for the receipt.
Let me know if this works for you and we will start resending them the updated receipt numbers.

Hi Heath,

Thank you for reissuing the receipt numbers for Kiss Goodbye to MS donors.

If you could please resend the confirmation emails including the new receipts at your earliest convenience, that would be much appreciated.

For Kiss Goodbye to MS donors, please include the below message and send Jason and myself a quick email once this has been actioned.

Cheers,

Tanja

Dear <First Name>,

Thank you for your generous donation of <$X,XXX> in support of <Fundraiser Name> on <XX/XX/XXXX/> [or if they didn't support a fundraiser it should read MS Research Australia. We really appreciate your support of life-changing multiple sclerosis (MS) research!

We're getting in touch to inform you that there was a temporary error with donation receipting from the Kiss Goodbye to MS website, which has now been rectified. Unfortunately the website issued duplicate donation receipt numbers and as every donation requires a unique receipt number, we have reissued your unique donation receipt for you, please see attached and below for your reference. Sincere apologies for this inconvenience.

Please note that you have not been charged again for this donation. Please disregard the previous receipt sent to you and only use the attached receipt for your records.

If you have any questions, please send us an email to kgtms@msra.org.au or give us a call on 1300 785 717.

Our sincere apologies again for the inconvenience. We appreciate your understanding.

Kindest regards,

Tanja & the Kiss Goodbye to MS team

Hi Jason, 

Confirming we have updated the receipt numbers and attached. Let us know if you need a hand resending the confirmations.

@heath Sorry for the delay.

I have to update some stuff on the entry so its ready to resend the notification. 

Please see the attached.

Hi Jason, 

Sure, we will schedule this for completion after-hours today.

Hi Heath,

Can you please recreate the receipt numbers in the initial instance? Tanja will be coming back to you with regards to sending an email out with the new receipt numbers issued but they would like to choose a message to go with it to support an explanation to our supporters why they are being reissued a receipt.

But as we need to close things off for April if you can reissue receipt numbers now, and give us a list of the impacted donations with the new receipt numbers issued, that would be great.

Let me know if you need any clarification.

Thanks,

Jason

Kind regards



Jason Cahill

Database Manager

MS Research Australia

Hi Jason, 

Confirming we have now isolated and fixed the issue. It was cause by a manual donation/offline donation being added as these trigger a different prefix/naming convention in the system. We have now add a loop to check for this exact scenario and moving forward the receipts will be generated as expected. 

With the receipts that have been assigned the number of KGTMS-1, do you want us to manually create their receipt numbers and re-email them to the donors?

Hi Jason, 

Sure, looking into this now and we will keep you updated.
@joel can you please look into this one as a priority. Thanks

action.text: Joel Maligalig assigned to Joel Maligalig

Hi Heath,

All of our receipt numbers on the KGTMS site are issuing KGTMS-1 instead of issuing a unique receipt number? Can you please investigate this and find out why this is happening and fix it? I was certain this issue was fixed before. We also need to be able to issue unique receipt numbers to these people, can you please propose what we should do to rectify this matter?

Thanks,

Jason

Kind regards
